message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper deals with machine comprehension of spoken content, which falls under the subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of subword units and data augmentation are techniques commonly used in NLP, which suggests that the paper may belong to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The dataset released in the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SD (Sound) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper's focus on mitigating the impact of ASR errors suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-category cs.LG (Learning).
